# Filament v5 — the bass: dark, fast, RUBBERY. The opposite pole from
# the heliograph lead (4bit-9d's law: bass = the fast dark layer).
# Character comes from interaction, not a preset shape: a resonant
# ladder nearly closed (480 Hz, res 1.2) with a fast modest filter
# kick gives every note a dark "wub" articulation; an octave-down saw
# under the pulse plus a breath of FM keeps the low end grainy and
# animal; the ARP circuit for snap; a whisper of shared noise so fast
# runs spit slightly. key_track 0.25 so it stays in the dark even
# when the line climbs. Releases in 90 ms so 32nd skitters speak.
waveform 1
pulse_width 0.24
osc2_wave 2
osc2_pitch -12
osc2_level 0.4
osc3_wave 0
osc3_pitch 0
osc3_level 0
detune 2
sub 0.25
circuit 1
key_track 0.25
osc_fm 0.1
sync 0
ring 0
glide 0
attack 0.004
decay 0.45
sustain 0.6
release 0.09
filter_env 0.9
filter_attack 0.002
filter_decay 0.12
filter_sustain 0.35
filter_release 0.1
cutoff 480
resonance 1.2
drive 2.4
saturation 1.1
hpf 28
volume 0.5
octave 4
noise 0.05
fuzz 0
spring 0
lfo_rate 0.5
lfo_shape 0.5
lfo_pitch 0
lfo_filter 0
lfo_pwm 0
